%pyspark
# Loading the various datasets into spark dataframes

info = spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/info.csv")
h1 = spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/Heartrate new.csv")
w3 = spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/weight3.csv")
w4 = spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/weight4.csv")
d3= spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/dailyactivity3.csv")
d4 = spark.read.format("csv").options(header="true", infeschema="true").load("/shared/users/raj1/dailyactivity4.csv")

%pyspark
#Appending datasets over succesive years
w3.createOrReplaceTempView("w3")
w4.createOrReplaceTempView("w4")
w = spark.sql("SELECT * from w3 union all SELECT * from w4 ")
z.show(w)

%pyspark
#Appending datasets over succesive years
d3.createOrReplaceTempView("d3")
d4.createOrReplaceTempView("d4")
d = spark.sql("SELECT * from d3 union all SELECT * from d4 ")
z.show(d)
h1.createOrReplaceTempView("h1")
h = spark.sql("SELECT participant_id,heart_rate from h1")
#z.show(h)

%pyspark
#Considering relevant features from each dataframes
w.createOrReplaceTempView("w")
f1 = spark.sql("SELECT participant_id,weight_pounds,bmi from w")
z.show(f1)

%pyspark
#Considering relevant features from each dataframes
d.createOrReplaceTempView("d")
f2= spark.sql("select participant_id,very_active_minutes,fairly_active_minutes,lightly_active_minutes,sedentary_minutes,calories from d")
z.show(f2)

%pyspark
#Considering relevant features from each dataframes and merging the features with the Healthcare Dataset
info.createOrReplaceTempView("info")
f1.createOrReplaceTempView("f1")
final_data= spark.sql("select distinct insurance,info.participant_id, smoker,dependants,age,sex,weight_pounds,bmi from info LEFT JOIN f1 on info.participant_id=f1.participant_id")
z.show(final_data)
#insurance column is the one we would like to predict

%pyspark
#Considering relevant features from each dataframes and merging the featuresto create the resulting Dataframe
final_data.createOrReplaceTempView("final_data")
f2.createOrReplaceTempView("f2")
final_data2= spark.sql("select distinct final_data.insurance,final_data.participant_id,final_data.smoker,final_data.dependants,final_data.age,final_data.sex,final_data.weight_pounds,final_data.bmi,f2.very_active_minutes,f2.fairly_active_minutes,f2.lightly_active_minutes,f2.sedentary_minutes,f2.calories from final_data LEFT JOIN f2 on final_data.participant_id=f2.participant_id")
z.show(final_data2)

%pyspark
#Including heart-rate data into the aforementioned resulting dataframe
h.createOrReplaceTempView("h")
final_data2.createOrReplaceTempView("final_data2")
data= spark.sql("select distinct final_data2.insurance,final_data2.participant_id,final_data2.smoker,final_data2.dependants,final_data2.age,final_data2.sex,final_data2.weight_pounds,final_data2.bmi,final_data2.very_active_minutes,final_data2.fairly_active_minutes,final_data2.lightly_active_minutes,final_data2.sedentary_minutes,final_data2.calories,h.heart_rate from final_data2 LEFT JOIN h on final_data2.participant_id=h.participant_id ")
z.show(data)

%pyspark
# Converting the schema to interger to perform future calculations and the model also requires all the values to be integer type to predict
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType
data=data.withColumn("weight_pounds", data["weight_pounds"].cast(IntegerType()))
data=data.withColumn("insurance", data["insurance"].cast(IntegerType()))
data=data.withColumn("bmi", data["bmi"].cast(IntegerType()))
data.show()
data.write.csv('/shared/users/raj1/processed_data.csv')

import org.apache.spark.sql.Row
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LabeledPoint
import org.apache.spark.mllib.util.MLUtils
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
import org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.RegressionMetrics
import org.apache.spark.ml.regression.LinearRegressionModel;
import org.apache.spark.ml.regression.LinearRegressionTrainingSummary;
import org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.Vectors;
import org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset;
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row;
import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession;
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.RegressionEvaluator
import org.apache.spark.ml.regression.LinearRegression
import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.{ParamGridBuilder, TrainValidationSplit}
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.ProbabilisticClassifier
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.LogisticRegression
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.{Evaluator, MulticlassClassificationEvaluator}
import org.apache.spark.ml.regression.LinearRegression
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.MulticlassMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.BinaryClassificationMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.classification.LogisticRegressionWithLBFGS
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{BinaryLogisticRegressionSummary, LogisticRegression}
import sqlContext.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame;
import org.apache.spark.sql.SQLContext;


val data = spark.read.format("csv").option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED").csv("/shared/users/raj1/processed_data.csv")
val data1  = data.withColumn("_c2", data("_c2").cast(IntegerType))
val data2  = data1.withColumn("_c3", data1("_c3").cast(IntegerType))
val data3  = data2.withColumn("_c4", data2("_c4").cast(IntegerType))
val data4  = data3.withColumn("_c5", data3("_c5").cast(IntegerType))
val data5  = data4.withColumn("_c6", data4("_c6").cast(IntegerType))
val data6  = data5.withColumn("_c7", data5("_c7").cast(IntegerType))
val data7  = data6.withColumn("_c8", data6("_c8").cast(IntegerType))
val data8  = data7.withColumn("_c9", data7("_c9").cast(IntegerType))
val data9  = data8.withColumn("_c10", data8("_c10").cast(IntegerType))
val data10  = data9.withColumn("_c11", data9("_c11").cast(IntegerType))
val data11  = data10.withColumn("_c12", data10("_c12").cast(IntegerType))
val data12  = data11.withColumn("_c13", data11("_c13").cast(IntegerType))

data12.printSchema
// create feature vector
val assembler =  new VectorAssembler()
  .setInputCols(Array("_c2", "_c4", "_c5", "_c6", "_c7","_c8","_c9","_c10","_c11","_c12","_c13"))
  .setOutputCol("features")
  
val df11 = assembler.transform(data12.na.drop).select($"_c0".cast(IntegerType).as("label"), $"features")



// Split the data into train and test
val splits = df11.randomSplit(Array(0.8,0.2), seed = 1234L)
val (train, test) = (splits(0), splits(1))

//Building the Linear Regression Model
val lr = new LinearRegression().setMaxIter(10)
  .setRegParam(0.3)
  .setElasticNetParam(0.8)
  
val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
  .addGrid(lr.regParam, Array(0.1, 0.01))
  .addGrid(lr.fitIntercept)
  .addGrid(lr.elasticNetParam, Array(0.0, 0.5, 1.0))
  .build()
  
val metric = "rmse"
val metric1= "r2"
val evaluator = new RegressionEvaluator()
  .setLabelCol("label")
  .setPredictionCol("prediction")
  .setMetricName(metric) 
  
// In this case the estimator is simply the linear regression.
// A TrainValidationSplit requires an Estimator, a set of Estimator ParamMaps, and an Evaluator.
val trainValidationSplit = new TrainValidationSplit()
  .setEstimator(lr)
  .setEvaluator(evaluator)
  .setTrainRatio(0.8)
  .setEstimatorParamMaps(paramGrid)

// Run train validation split, and choose the best set of parameters.
val model = trainValidationSplit.fit(train)

// Make predictions on test data. model is the model with combination of parameters
// that performed best.
println("Number of records accounted for prediction")
test.count()
val predictions=model.transform(test)
  .select("features", "label", "prediction")
predictions.show()
val rmse = evaluator.evaluate(predictions)
println(rmse)
